#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:3
msgid "Using Pyodide in a web worker"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:6
msgid ""
"Pyodide requires a module-type worker because `pyodide.asm.mjs` is an ES "
"module. Classic workers using `importScripts()` are not supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:10
msgid ""
"This document includes an example demonstrating how to use Pyodide to "
"execute Python scripts asynchronously in a web worker."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:13
msgid "Let's start with [the definition of a worker][worker api]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:15
msgid ""
"A worker is an object created using a constructor (e.g. [Worker()][worker "
"constructor]) that runs a named JavaScript file — this file contains the "
"code that will run in the worker thread; workers run in another global "
"context that is different from the current window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:20
msgid ""
"A lot of Python programs do long-running synchronous computations. Running "
"them in the main thread blocks the UI. Using a web worker is advantageous "
"because the Python code runs in a separate thread from your UI and does not "
"impact your application's responsiveness."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:25
msgid ""
"On the other hand, since workers run in a separate global context, you "
"cannot directly share globals between a worker and the main thread. In "
"particular, a worker cannot directly manipulate the DOM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:29
msgid "Detailed example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:31
msgid "In this example process we will have three parties involved:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:33
msgid ""
"The **web worker** is responsible for running scripts in its own separate "
"thread."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:34
msgid ""
"The **worker API** exposes a consumer-to-provider communication interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:35
msgid ""
"The **consumer**s want to run some scripts outside the main thread, so they "
"don't block the main thread."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:38
msgid "Consumers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:40
msgid ""
"Our goal is to run some Python code in another thread. This other thread "
"will not have access to the main thread objects. Therefore, we will need an "
"API that takes as input both the Python `script` we want to run and the "
"`context` on which it relies (some JavaScript variables that our code needs "
"access to). Let's first describe what API we would like to have."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:46
msgid ""
"Here is an example of consumer that will exchange with the web worker, via "
"`workerApi.mjs`. It runs the following Python `script` using the provided "
"`context` and a function called `asyncRun()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:50
msgid ""
"import { asyncRun } from \"./workerApi.js\";\n"
"\n"
"const script = `\n"
"    import statistics\n"
"    statistics.stdev(A_rank)\n"
"`;\n"
"\n"
"const context = {\n"
"  A_rank: [0.8, 0.4, 1.2, 3.7, 2.6, 5.8],\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"async function main() {\n"
"  const { result, error } = await asyncRun(script, context);\n"
"  if (result) {\n"
"    console.log(\"pyodideWorker result:\", result);\n"
"  } else if (error) {\n"
"    console.log(\"pyodideWorker error:\", error);\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"main();\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:74
msgid ""
"Before writing the API, let's first have a look at how the worker runs the "
"`script` using a given `context`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:77
msgid "Web worker"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:79
msgid "Here is the worker code:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:81
msgid ""
"// webworker.mjs\n"
"import { loadPyodide } from \"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/pyodide/dev/full/"
"pyodide.mjs\";\n"
"\n"
"let pyodideReadyPromise = loadPyodide();\n"
"\n"
"self.onmessage = async (event) => {\n"
"  // make sure loading is done\n"
"  const pyodide = await pyodideReadyPromise;\n"
"  const { id, python, context } = event.data;\n"
"  // Now load any packages we need, run the code, and send the result back.\n"
"  await pyodide.loadPackagesFromImports(python);\n"
"  // make a Python dictionary with the data from `context`\n"
"  const dict = pyodide.globals.get(\"dict\");\n"
"  const globals = dict(Object.entries(context));\n"
"  try {\n"
"    // Execute the python code in this context\n"
"    const result = await pyodide.runPythonAsync(python, { globals });\n"
"    self.postMessage({ result, id });\n"
"  } catch (error) {\n"
"    self.postMessage({ error: error.message, id });\n"
"  }\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:106
msgid "The worker API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:108
msgid ""
"Now that we established what the two sides need and how they operate, let's "
"connect them using an API that wraps the message passing code into an "
"asynchronous function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/webworker.md:112
msgid ""
"// workerApi.mjs\n"
"function getPromiseAndResolve() {\n"
"  let resolve;\n"
"  let promise = new Promise((res) => {\n"
"    resolve = res;\n"
"  });\n"
"  return { promise, resolve };\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"// Each message needs a unique id to identify the response. In a real "
"example,\n"
"// we might use a real uuid package\n"
"let lastId = 1;\n"
"function getId() {\n"
"  return lastId++;\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"// Add an id to msg, send it to worker, then wait for a response with the "
"same id.\n"
"// When we get such a response, use it to resolve the promise.\n"
"function requestResponse(worker, msg) {\n"
"  const { promise, resolve } = getPromiseAndResolve();\n"
"  const idWorker = getId();\n"
"  worker.addEventListener(\"message\", function listener(event) {\n"
"    if (event.data?.id !== idWorker) {\n"
"      return;\n"
"    }\n"
"    // This listener is done so remove it.\n"
"    worker.removeEventListener(\"message\", listener);\n"
"    // Filter the id out of the result\n"
"    const { id, ...rest } = event.data;\n"
"    resolve(rest);\n"
"  });\n"
"  worker.postMessage({ id: idWorker, ...msg });\n"
"  return promise;\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"const pyodideWorker = new Worker(\"./webworker.mjs\", { type: "
"\"module\" });\n"
"\n"
"export function asyncRun(script, context) {\n"
"  return requestResponse(pyodideWorker, {\n"
"    context,\n"
"    python: script,\n"
"  });\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
